# No automatic push or remote publish

Agents finish work **locally**. The user **pushes and merges manually every time**.

## Forbidden unless the user explicitly asks

Do **not** run any of the following unless the user clearly says to (e.g. "push", "push this branch", "merge the PR"):

- `git push` (any form, including `-u`, tags, or other remotes)
- `git push --force` / `--force-with-lease` / other force-push variants
- `gh pr merge` or any other command that merges or publishes a PR to the default branch
- Any other remote-publishing action that updates `origin` (or equivalent) without an explicit user request

Creating a PR with `gh pr create` still requires pushing the branch first. Only push when the user explicitly asks you to open/push a PR (or to push). If they only ask for local commits, stop after the commit and tell them what to push.

## Required finish state

When a task ends with git changes:

1. Make local commits on a branch as needed.
2. Do **not** push unless explicitly requested.
3. Tell the user exactly what to run (branch name, suggested `git push -u origin HEAD`, and/or that they can open/merge the PR themselves).

